    tast: Introduce testing.TestInfo.
    
    Formerly TestInstance had two purposes: (1) to represent a test
    instance registered to the global registry in bundles, (2) to
    send test information over wire among the tast command, runners and
    bundles.
    
    But this was known to be a tricky design because serializing and
    deserializing TestInstance does not yield the original TestInstance
    due to existence of runtime-only fields (e.g. Func, Pre, Val).
    
    This change finally solves the issue by introducing a small struct
    TestInfo dedicated for the second purpose of the original TestInstance.
    TestInfo is a simple struct consisting of JSON-serializable exported
    fields only. TestInstance is no longer JSON-serializable.
    
    Users of TestInstance are updated to use TestInfo instead whenever
    appropriate. In particular, control messages now deliver TestInfo
    instead of TestInstance.
    
    This is a pure refactoring; no functional change is expected.
    
    BUG=chromium:1091601
    BUG=chromium:984387
