    state: Fix State.HasError behavior.
    
    crrev.com/c/2217704 updated the test runner to create a new State
    object for every stage. This introduced a bug that State.HasError
    does not take into account errors reported by earlier stages, which
    caused the faillog to stop functioning because it never sees errors
    reported by tests/preconditions.
    
    This change fixes the issue by making top-level State inherit its
    parent RootState's error status. Note that State created by State.Run
    for a subtest does not inherit its parent State's error status so that
    subtests can see isolated error statuses.
    
    BUG=chromium:1092779
