Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Fri May 29 16:38:12 2020 +0900

    bundle: Abort execution if a test ignores its timeout.
    
    Today, if a test main function does not return soon after the context
    cancellation by the test timeout, Tast just lets the goroutine running
    and continue to the next test.
    
    We found that this is a problematic behavior because an abandoned
    goroutine may interact the next test badly, e.g. calling chrome.Close
    concurrently with chrome.New.
    
    Rather than continuing, we should abort the bundle execution when a test
    does not return. Fortunately the tast command has logic to restart test
    execution when runners/bundles exit before all tests are run, so we can
    continue from the next test.
    
    BUG=chromium:1087758
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
