    tast: Associate PreCtx with the first test.
    
    Historically the context.Context and testing.State given to
    preconditions are those for the first test. For example,
    testing.State.ContextOutDir returns the output directory for the
    first test. This is known to be a suboptimal design, but it is
    the current semantics.
    
    Currently the context returned by testing.State.PreCtx is not
    associated with any test, meaning that it cannot be used to call
    support libraries gated with current test checks, e.g. gRPC method
    calls (w/ testing.ContextServiceDeps) or chrome.New
    (w/ testing.ContextSoftwareDeps). This change associates it with
    the first test to be consistent with the existing semantics.
    
