Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Thu Feb 27 16:54:49 2020 +0900

    tast: Rework test instantiation.
    
    A new function "instantiate" is the new central place to construct
    test instances (TestInstance) from a test declaration (Test). It
    validates the given test declaration, generates one or more test
    instances from a base test and its parameters, and then validates
    the generated test instances.
    
    Formerly most validation steps were performed against test
    declarations rather than generated test instances. This was actually
    problematic because attribute validation (e.g. "crosbolt_weekly"
    should appear together with "group:crosbolt") should be done after
    combining attributes from a base test and its parameters. With this
    change, only minimal number of validation steps are performed for
    test declarations (in particular consistency checks among sibling
    parameters), and other validations are performed against generated
    test instances.
    
    BUG=chromium:1005041
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    
    Cq-Depend: chromium:2077378
