    tast-lint: Support service declarations.
    
    With the arrival of gRPC support, Go files that used to be called
    "test main files" may contain gRPC service implementations instead
    of test main functions. A gRPC service is defined like this:
    
      // example_service.go
    
      func init() {
          testing.AddService(&testing.Service{
              Register: func(srv *grpc.Server, s *testing.ServiceState) {
                  pb.RegisterExampleServer(srv, &Example{s: s})
              },
          })
      }
    
      type Example struct {
          s *testing.ServiceState
      }
    
      func (*Example) Hello(ctx context.Context, ...) (..., error) {
          ...
      }
    
    Thus we rename "test main files" to "entry files", and update
    check.Exports to allow exporting a single type (gRPC service
    implementation) instead of a test main function.
    
    BUG=chromium:969627
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    
