Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Wed Oct 23 18:50:40 2019 +0900

    tast: Add ServiceDeps to testing.Test.
    
    ServiceDeps enumerates gRPC service names the test may access.
    The field is useful for remote tests only.
    
    Attempts to call gRPC services not declared in ServiceDeps will be
    rejected. We enforce the rule for two purposes:
    
    1. If a remote test calls gRPC services requiring external data
       files, they should be downloaded before the remote test starts.
       By forcing remote tests to declare service dependencies, we can
       ask local test bundle executable to download required external
       data files in advance.
    2. It makes clear which remote tests use a particular gRPC service.
       We can delete a gRPC service if there is no caller.
    
    BUG=chromium:969627
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    
    Change-Id: Iadd4d78d78011933467f466a36a9cc7a0389057b
