    tast: Immediately unblock wait operations on Abort.
    
    Previously Abort just called Session.Signal(SIGKILL) and hoped the
    server to finish the command execution soon. However it is not
    always the case and Session.Wait can block until the context
    deadline. This is usually an undesired behavior.
    
    With this change, Wait/Run/Output/CombinedOutput returns
    immediately after calling Abort. SIGKILL is still sent to the
    remote process (in waitAndClose), but the timing is changed to
    when Wait/Run/Output/CombinedOutput is called.
    
    BUG=chromium:971024
    BUG=chromium:969627
