Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Tue Sep 10 10:19:20 2019 +0900

    tast: Fix a race condition in TestGetFileTimeout.
    
    This test makes sure that Host.GetFile fails if the given context
    is canceled during its execution.
    
    Previously cancellation was performed by setting td.execTimeout
    to endTimeout, which instructs testData.handleExec to cancel the
    context just before a SSH command finishes. In the case of this
    test, the SSH command is /bin/tar creating a tarball. However
    actually its return code is ignored in GetFile; instead, exit code
    of the local /bin/tar command connected via pipe is checked.
    
    So, as opposed to the test's original intention, when the test
    passed, the error was reported from the local /bin/tar due to
    context cancellation. This is actually a race condition; the local
    tar command can exit successfully before the context is canceled.
    This race condition can be reproduced reliably by inserting
    time.Sleep(time.Second) before td.cancel() in testData.handleExec.
    
    This change fixes the race condition by using startTimeout which
    cancels the context before a remote SSH command is executed. This
    should preserve the original intention of the test.
    
    BUG=chromium:1002191
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    
    Change-Id: I5430e2e79d11fb032a1695a6eac90497c0cb39f5
