Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Sat Aug 24 02:29:22 2019 +0900

    tast: Decide the output directory of local tests in the tast command.
    
    Previously the output directory which local test bundles write
    test artifacts to was decided by the local_test_runner and the
    directory path was notified to the tast command by a RunEnd
    control message sent at the end of all tests.
    
    This is problematic in two points:
    - When local_test_runner is aborted for timeout or crashes,
      RunEnd is not sent and thus it is impossible to locate and
      pull test artifacts.
    - When local_test_runner is restarted for crashes, test
      artifacts are written to different directories every time.
    
    This change makes the tast command always set OutDir in its
    RunTests request (runner.Args.RunTests.BundleArgs.OutDir) by
    generating a random directory name. Runners are also updated
    to create the output directory if it does not exist.
    
    For protocol compatibility, RunEnd.OutDir is still filled, and
    the tast command issues a mkdir command via SSH to create the
    output directory before running local_test_runner so that the
    new tast command works well with older local_test_runner.
    
    The change to fix the issue that test artifacts are not saved
    when the global timeout is hit is coming next.
    
    BUG=chromium:972457
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    TEST=fast_build.sh
    TEST=~/go/bin/tast run -build=false DUT example.Perf
    TEST=~/go/bin/tast run -build=true DUT example.Perf
    
