Author: Shuhei Takahashi <nya@chromium.org>
Date:   Thu Jul 11 15:09:43 2019 +0900

    tast: Introduce os/exec-style interface for SSH.
    
    Properly using golang.org/x/crypto/ssh to run commands via SSH
    is difficult for several reasons:
    
    - The ssh package does not support context.Context. To avoid
      freezes, we need to use background goroutines carefully.
    - The ssh package only allows invoking shells. This is a natural
      restriction due to SSH protocol itself, but using this interface
      directly would lead to fragile programs with random shell escapes.
    
    To absorb these difficulties we need a wrapper. Today we have
    SSH.Run, SSH.Start, SSHCommandHandle for this purpose, but it does
    not resolve these two issues completely.
    
    This change introduces an os/exec-style interface that solves
    these issues.
    
    To keep this CL short, it does not modify the existing users of
    SSHCommandHandle, but modifies SSHCommandHandle itself to use the
    new Cmd internally. Next CL will remove SSHCommandHandle and
    update the callers to directly use the new Cmd.
    
    BUG=chromium:971024
    TEST=fast_build.sh -T
    TEST=fast_build.sh && ~/go/bin/tast run betty arc.Boot
    
