    tast: Diagnose SSH connection aborts.
    
    When the SSH connection to the target aborted on running local
    tests, run the following diagnosis:
    
    - On connecting to the target first time, record boot_id.
    - If the SSH connection aborted, try reconnecting to the target
      up to 1 minute.
    - Compare boot_id with the recorded one. If it's the same, the
      target did not reboot, so it is likely the connection was aborted
      by network issues.
    - Read the last 1000 lines of systemd journal from the previous
      boot. If the log contains a message from pre-shutdown, the target
      rebooted normally.
    - Read console-ramoops file. If the log contains crashes, the
      target rebooted for a kernel crash.
    
