    tast: Support retrying SSH connection attempts.
    
    Add an -sshretries flag to the "run" and "list" subcommands
    that can be used to specify the number of times to retry SSH
    connection attempts. Also add a ConnectRetries field to
    host.SSHOptions and add a RejectConns method to
    test.SSHServer that can be used to simulate failures.
    
    The flag defaults to 0 since I think that that's what most
    developers will want, but I plan to set it to 2 when Tast is
    run in the lab to see if it helps with connection errors
    (presumably caused by network flakiness) that have been seen
    when collecting DUT system information in the lab.
    
    Also attempt to resolve a long-standing TODO about SSH
    connections being leaked in the unlikely event that they
    take longer than the context's deadline but still succeed
    eventually.
    
