    runner: Unify the code paths for report/non-report mode.
    
    We used to have slightly different logics in runTestsAndReport
    (report-mode; used when the test runner is run by "tast" command)
    and runTestsAndLog (non-report mode; used when the test runner is
    run directly).
    
    This change unifies the two funcs by making runTestsAndLog to call
    runTestsAndReport and convert its control message output to textual
    logs. Fortunately runTestsAndReport already parses control messages
    from bundles, so the only new message type to process is RunError,
    which now contains the exit status code to return.
    
    Several functions are updated to return *StatusError instead of
    error to make it statically safe to extract an exit code.
    
