    tast: Refactor Test.Run to use stages.
    
    Generalize the testing package's code for running a test
    into a runStages function that runs a series of functions
    (currently setup, test, cleanup) within a goroutine. Each
    function has its own timeout, which is a departure from the
    old model of also allocating the test's timeout to setup and
    cleanup. This paves the way for granting longer timeouts to
    preconditions in the future.
    
    The "tast run" command limits the amount of time that it
    waits for the next control message (to avoid hanging
    indefinitely if the DUT becomes unresponsive), so this
    change also adds a new Test.AdditionalTime field that the
    bundle uses to pass back extra time allocated to setup and
    cleanup functions.
    
